https://haydenjames.io/linux-securely-copy-files-using-scp/

Copy file from a remote host to local host SCP example:

$ scp username@from_host:file.txt /local/directory/
 

Copy file from local host to a remote host SCP example:

$ scp file.txt username@to_host:/remote/directory/


Copying Files with a Specific Port â€“ In this example, we specify a custom SSH port (2222) for the SCP connection:

$ scp -P 2222 username@from_host:file.txt /local/directory/
